DESCRIPTION:Join us for a scenic 9KM waterfront ride featuring harbour view
 s\, historic neighbourhoods\, and a unique ferry crossing experience. 🚴‍♀️
 ⛴️<br><br>We will depart from the Emera Oval to Halifax Ferry Terminal\, wh
 ere we'll board the ferry for a relaxing harbour crossing to Alderney Termi
 nal\, ride within Dartmouth and head back to Halifax. ⛴️<br><br>This is a f
 riendly\, moderate-paced ride with sweeps provided to ensure no one is left
  behind but please note that we will encounter some fairly steep hills alon
 g the way.<br><br><b>Requirements:</b><br><br>All participants must complet
 e a <a href="https://cyclehalifax.ca/waiver">waiver</a> before the ride  📝
 <br>Ferry tickets must be purchased individually 🎫<br><br><b>Details: </b>
 <br><br>Distance: 9KM 📏<br>Estimated Elevation: 131 m<br>Start: 8:00 AM at
  Emera Oval (8:15 AM departure) ⏰<br>Pace: Moderate\, with sweeps provided
 🚴‍♂️
LAST-MODIFIED:20250825T145502Z
LOCATION:Emera Oval\, 5775 Cogswell St\, Halifax\, NS B3K 4B2\, Canada
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:The Ferry Loop Ride
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20250608
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20250609
DTSTAMP:20260601T230038Z
UID:1go0770ua6lpj299d3upn51ns6@google.com
CREATED:20250413T150639Z
DESCRIPTION:Take the Long Way Home <br>Loco Loop (200km)Meet at the Halifax
  Oval at 5:45am <br> <br><br>More info: <br><a href="https://www.instagram.
 com/p/DHV2ak1RYE8/?img_index=4" target="_blank">https://www.instagram.com/p
 /DHV2ak1RYE8/?img_index=4</a><br> <br><span dir="auto"><span>TMC &amp\; <a
 href="https://www.instagram.com/tip2tip_ns/">@tip2tip_ns</a> creator <a hre
 f="https://www.instagram.com/ashleigh.myles/">@ashleigh.myles</a> will be h
 osting four fun and challenging rides around HRM designed to give you a tas
 te of what riding longer\, faster and farther feels like. <br><br>Starting
 on April 5th\, we’ll be riding consecutively longer rides until the last on
 e in June. To make it to the end of each ride\, we’ll be riding an average
 of 20-22km/h with breaks for snacks. We’ll be in close communication throug
 hout the rides on WhatsApp to ensure everyone’s feeling good and will chat
 through some bail options at the start of each ride in case you need to dip
  early. <br><br>As always\, this is a safe space to test your limits! We en
 courage you to regularly check in with yourself and to be open about how yo
 u’re making out.<br><br>These rides ARE NOT our typical no-drop monthly soc
 ial rides\, so keep an eye out for our first social ride happening in late
 April!<br><br>⚡️⚡️ These rides ARE for women\, trans\, and gender diverse f
 olks ⚡️⚡️<br><br>Check out our linktree for the ride routes!<br><br>If you
 have any questions\, concerns\, or accessibility needs that affect your par
 ticipation please let us know\, however you’re comfortable. We want these r
 ides to help us all gain confidence on bikes! Let us know how we can make t
 hat happen. <br><br>Check yer brakes and we’ll see you soon! <br></span></s
 pan>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260404T092425Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:5:45am: Monthly Cycle (200km)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
