DESCRIPTION:🕐 Time: 6-8 pm<br>📍 Meet-up location: At the waterfront gazeb
 o behind the Discovery Centre (44°38'33.8"N 63°34'01.8"W)<br>🚲 Distance: 1
 1.3 km<br><br>📖 Topic:<br>- Road signs and hand signals recap from last ti
 me<br><br>✏️ Time Table:<br>6-6:30 pm: Mini Urban Course<br>6:30-7:30 pm: P
 ractice Ride<br>7:30-8 pm: Extra Time for questions and feedback<br><a href
 ="goog_764846435"><br></a><br><a href="https://linktr.ee/cyclehalifax">Chec
 k out the linktree for:</a><br>- Waiver<br>- Detailed ride route<br><br>Get
  ready to explore the city on two wheels in this fun and interactive event.
  Whether you're a beginner or a seasoned cyclist\, this course is perfect f
 or anyone looking to enhance their urban biking skills. Join us for an even
 ing filled with tips on navigating urban roads\, bike handling techniques\,
  and safety guidelines. Don't miss this opportunity to boost your cycling c
 onfidence and enjoy a ride through the city with fellow biking enthusiasts.
  See you there!<br><br>*If we need to cancel due to weather conditions\, we
  will post a notice on this website at least 3 hours before the day of the
 ride.
LAST-MODIFIED:20240817T133407Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Mini Urban Cycling Course
TRANSP:OPAQUE
