DESCRIPTION:Monthly Cycle: Take the Long Way Home <br>100km Ride: Porters L
 ake Loop <br>Meet at Halifax Oval at 7:45am<br><br>More info: <br><a href="
 https://www.instagram.com/p/DHV2ak1RYE8/?img_index=1" target="_blank">https
 ://www.instagram.com/p/DHV2ak1RYE8/?img_index=1</a><br> <br><span dir="auto
 "><span>TMC &amp\; <a href="https://www.instagram.com/tip2tip_ns/">@tip2tip
 _ns</a> creator <a href="https://www.instagram.com/ashleigh.myles/">@ashlei
 gh.myles</a> will be hosting four fun and challenging rides around HRM desi
 gned to give you a taste of what riding longer\, faster and farther feels l
 ike. <br><br>Starting on April 5th\, we’ll be riding consecutively longer r
 ides until the last one in June. To make it to the end of each ride\, we’ll
  be riding an average of 20-22km/h with breaks for snacks. We’ll be in clos
 e communication throughout the rides on WhatsApp to ensure everyone’s feeli
 ng good and will chat through some bail options at the start of each ride i
 n case you need to dip early. <br><br>As always\, this is a safe space to t
 est your limits! We encourage you to regularly check in with yourself and t
 o be open about how you’re making out.<br><br>These rides ARE NOT our typic
 al no-drop monthly social rides\, so keep an eye out for our first social r
 ide happening in late April!<br><br>⚡️⚡️ These rides ARE for women\, trans\
 , and gender diverse folks ⚡️⚡️<br><br>Check out our linktree for the ride
 routes!<br><br>If you have any questions\, concerns\, or accessibility need
 s that affect your participation please let us know\, however you’re comfor
 table. We want these rides to help us all gain confidence on bikes! Let us
 know how we can make that happen. <br><br>Check yer brakes and we’ll see yo
 u soon! <br></span></span>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260404T092425Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:7:45am: Monthly Cycle (100km)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
