DESCRIPTION:📅 Date: July 26\n🕐 Time: 6-8 pm\n📍 Meet-up location: At the
 waterfront gazebo behind the Discovery Centre (44°38'33.8"N 63°34'01.8"W)\n
 🚲 Distance: 11.3 km\n\n📖 Topic:\n- Hand-Signs\n- Road Signs\n- How to Cro
 ss the MacDonald Bridge\n- How to bring your bike onto the ferry\n*Please b
 ring your own bus pass\, but we also have 10 tickets for those who don't ha
 ve a bus pass.\n\n✏️ Time Table:\n6-6:30 pm: Mini Urban Course\n6:30-7:30 p
 m: Practice Ride\n7:30-8 pm: Extra Time for questions and feedback\n\nGet r
 eady to explore the city on two wheels in this fun and interactive event. W
 hether you're a beginner or a seasoned cyclist\, this course is perfect for
  anyone looking to enhance their urban biking skills. Join us for an evenin
 g filled with tips on navigating urban roads\, bike handling techniques\, a
 nd safety guidelines. Don't miss this opportunity to boost your cycling con
 fidence and enjoy a ride through the city with fellow biking enthusiasts. S
 ee you there!\n\n*If we need to cancel due to weather conditions\, we will
 post a notice on this website at least 3 hours before the day of the ride.
LAST-MODIFIED:20240817T134354Z
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Mini Urban Cycling Course
TRANSP:OPAQUE
