DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1ED8wSPKgmiNc4ytnIus59
 z7W2SoepMDI/view?usp=drive_link"><b>Attachments</b></a><br><br>Dear support
 er of healthy communities:<br><br>The Halifax Regional Municipality and CAA
  Atlantic invite you to join Mayor Mike Savage and Regional Councillors for
  the 11th annual Mayor’s Bike Ride on Monday\, September 16\, 2024 (11:30 a
 .m. to 1:30 p.m.). The Mayor’s Ride aims to promote cycling and celebrate t
 he contributions to active transportation in the municipality by supporters
  of healthy and active communities (like you!).<br><br>This year’s ride beg
 ins at the Dartmouth side of the Angus L. Macdonald Bridge (30 Faulkner St\
 , Dartmouth\, NS). The route will explore Dartmouth by bike via the Wyse Ro
 ad bike lanes\, Dartmouth Common Greenway\, Dahlia local street bikeway\, S
 hubie Canal Greenway past Sullivan’s Pond Park and along Lake Banook. The r
 ide will end with a reception and lunch at the Kiwanis Graham’s Grove Park.
 <br><br>Spread the word — everyone’s invited!<br><br><b>Details</b><br>• Da
 te: Monday\, September 16\, 2024<br>• Time: 11:30 a.m. to 1:30 p.m.<br>• St
 arting location: 30 Faulkner St\, Dartmouth\, NS B3A 3A5 (Halifax Harbour B
 ridges)<br>• Ending location: Kiwanis Graham’s Grove Park with reception an
 d lunch provided.<br>• All are welcome<br><br><b>Tips</b><br>• Please arriv
 e before 11:30 a.m.<br>• Bikes and helmets are required for the ride<br>• H
 alifax Regional Police will be providing an escort<br>• The route is approx
 imately 3 kilometers<br>• Accessible washrooms are available at the Kiwanis
  Graham’s Grove Park<br>• Bring water for the ride<br><br>Rain Date: Friday
 \, September 20\, 2024 (11:30 a.m. to 1:30 p.m.)<br>Note: Attendees are enc
 ouraged to bike or bus to the event. Parking is not available on the Halifa
 x Harbour<br>Bridges property. There is some on-street parking on Lyle Stre
 et\, and on surrounding streets.
LAST-MODIFIED:20240827T182558Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Mayor's Bike Ride
TRANSP:OPAQUE
